title: Upper Green River
description: Underwater footage of Mark's swim through the shallow headwaters of the Green River

title: Fresh start
description: Start of the Mark's swim at the headwaters of the Green-Duwamish River: trickles of water down the steep slopes of Blowout Mountain

title: Full of life
description: Tumbling, green oxygenated cold water alive with fish in the headwaters of the Green, which runs into the Duwamish. Unlimited visibility, crystal clear water

title: Things get chilly
description: Washington's only ghost town: Lester. Coldest swim of the journey: water only 42 degrees, air temperature 32 degrees. Icicles on the twigs overhanging the banks
Saw a bobcat

title: Steelhead
description: Saw first adult steelhead, many other fish, mostly young salmon and steelhead.

title: River otters and inner tubers
description: First bottles and cans. Inner tubers. Saw an eagle, crawdaddy eating a dead fish. Saw a family of three river otters playing. Saw a frog holding in a hidey hole underwater. Fishing lure and line snagged on a stick in the river.

title: Things get warm
description: Farms, cows. People swimming. Hottest swim of the journey, water 73 degrees. Air temperature over 90 degrees. Lots of birds: mergansers, kingfishers, great blue herons.

title: Whirlpool
description: Interesting whirlpool behind a rock. Big schools of salmon. Tall cottonwood and maple trees on river banks.

title: "A big pile of clothes"
description: Big log jam blocks the river, walked around it. Found first discarded junk in the river: a big pile of clothes. Three barking dogs making a commotion. Farms transitioning to suburbs.

title: A watch
description: Saw three mink. Found a discarded bicycle, a scooter, and a desk under a bridge. Found a working watch, white with a white band. Still using it.

title: Pink salmon
description: First adult pink salmon in the river.

title: Trash and restoration
description: Habitat restoration project, including side channel for young fish to rest. Discarded skateboard with fishing lure in it. Huge truck tire in the river. Shopping cart. Irrigation pipe taking water from river.

title: Spawning
description: Swam with thousands and thousands of pink salmon, even touched one. Lots of salmon jumping.

title: Treasure hunters
description: Two guys in wet suits: junk pickers looking for treasures in the river, harvested into floating rafts. Soccer ball drifts by. Salmon jumping.

title: Duwamish begins
description: Green River turns into the Duwamish at this point. River is surrounded by freeways. Train tracks next to river. Washing machine in the river. Roar of traffic. Ocean tides reach this high in the river.

title: Things get cloudy
description: River getting murky, hard to see. Lots of fishermen, and some are getting lots of fish. Industry and highways all around and along the river. Visibility low as five feet, hard to see anything underwater.

title: Salty water and sea lions
description: Shoreline developed with docks, pilings, loading and unloading ramps, marinas. Heavy industry, most of shoreline is human-constructed. Lots of stormdrains. Osprey eating a salmon. Water getting salty and cooler. Sea lions in distance. Tribal fishing nets catching salmon.

title: Cargo
description: Encountering the Duwamish Diagonal: the biggest storm drain in Seattle, maybe ten feet wide and across.  Duwamish tribal longhouse. heavy industry, cargo shipping terminal, cranes, stacks of cargo containers.

title: Choppy waters
description: Sea lions come close; they are very big! Windy, water is rough. It's hard to swim.
